# {{context|legal|lang=en}} A pair of [[identical]] [[document]]s executed by two people in order to insure identical dispositions of their property upon the [[death]] of either or both.

====Usage notes====
The mirror will differs from the [[mutual will]] in that the latter is intended as a [[contract]], made [[irrevocable]] by the agreement of both [[testator]]s to execute the document.

